    "content": "nullNonprofit Cloud\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Nonprofit Cloud\n What's Included in Nonprofit Cloud\n Create a Nonprofit Cloud Trial Org\n Einstein Copilot in Nonprofit Cloud (Beta)\n Set Up Nonprofit Cloud\n Fundraising\n Get Started with Fundraising\n Learn About Nonprofit Cloud for Fundraising\n Set Up Fundraising\n Gift Commitments\n Add a Gift Commitment\n Enter In-Kind Gift Commitments\n Add a Designation to a Gift Commitment\n Schedule a Gift Commitment\n Gift Commitments\n Gift Commitment Processing\n Gift Transactions\n Gift Designations\n Gift Entry and Processing\n Manage Constituent Addresses\n Gift Acknowledgments and Tax Receipts\n Gift and Donor Trends with Rollups\n Outreach Source Codes\n Scoring Frameworks Help Increase Fundraising Success\n Donor Profiles\n Copilot Actions: Fundraising Gift Proposals (Beta)\n Donor Support Profiles\n Program Management\n Case Management\n Outcome Management with Nonprofit Cloud\n Nonprofit Cloud for Grantmaking\n Nonprofit Cloud and Translation\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nNONPROFIT CLOUD\nGift Commitments\n\nUse the Fundraising app to manage all types of gift commitments, both monetary and in kind. You can track gifts for particular opportunities and campaigns, change transaction schedules, and update donation amounts. Automated tasks simplify handling recurring donations. You can also easily monitor upcoming, missed, failed, and recently paid and refunded transactions.\n\nAdd a Gift Commitment\nCreate a record for a multi-payment pledge or recurring gift, including the schedule, amount, and gift designations of the donor’s choice. You can connect the gift to a campaign or opportunity and allocate the gift for a particular designation.\nEnter In-Kind Gift Commitments\nAn in-kind gift is a donation of goods or services, rather than a cash donation, to a nonprofit organization. To enter in-kind gifts into Salesforce, enter them as gift commitments.\nAdd a Designation to a Gift Commitment\nAllocate or reallocate gift amounts associated with a gift commitment to gift designations of the donor's choice.\nSchedule a Gift Commitment\nSchedule a recurring or custom payment of a gift commitment from a donor. The scheduling options change based on the schedule type that you select when you create the gift commitment.\nGift Commitments\nYou can change the gift amount, schedule, and payment instrument details of a gift commitment. When you update the gift commitment record, Fundraising automatically processes the commitment and its associated records, such as the transaction and schedule.\nGift Commitment Processing\nFundraising offers a structured and automated method to manage and process gift commitments based on the associated gift commitment schedule and gift transactions.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
